---
description: MUI layout and visual styles must use sx, not DOM/system props
globs: App/**/*.{tsx,jsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

# MUI styling: use `sx` only

For `@mui/material` components (`Box`, `Stack`, `Typography`, etc.):

- Put **layout and visual styles** in `sx={{ ... }}` (e.g. `display`, `flexDirection`, `alignItems`, `flexWrap`, `gap`, `justifyContent`, padding, colors).
- Do **not** pass those as top-level props (`alignItems`, `flexWrap`, `justifyContent`, `spacing`, etc.) — they can leak to the DOM and trigger React warnings.
- `sx` on the MUI component is fine; avoid duplicating the same styles on `component` wrappers.

```tsx
// Bad
<Stack direction="row" spacing={1} alignItems="center" flexWrap="wrap">

// Good
<Stack sx={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: 1 }}>
```

Semantic MUI props that are not CSS (e.g. `component`, `href`, `onClick`, `size` on `Button`/`Chip`) are still OK.
